dc:description: Dolichocephalic cranium (a) with RM1-2. There is extensive alveolar resorption, the vault is anteroposteriorly oblong, and the sagittal, lambdoidal and lambdoidal sutures are obliterated, although individual was probably not old. Mandible (b) with some teeth, and resorbed LM2 alveolus.
